               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0204SDGM">Ṣäbäla Dabra Gannat Māryām / SDGM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1934" notAfter="1935">According to the colophon the Ms.
                        was written in 1927, probably the year of mercy (= 1934/35 A.D.).
 Liqä
                        ṗāṗāsāt ʾabbā Qerǝllos (Metropolitan Qerǝllos IV, in tenure 1929-47, cp. EAE
                        IV, 291-292) and ṗāṗās ʾabbā Yǝsḥaq (Bishop of Tǝgray, in tenure 1929-1954,
                        cp. BGY-014) are mentioned on <locus target="#39ra">39ra</locus>, 41ra,
                        47ra. King Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I (r. 1930-74) is mentioned on <locus target="#39vb">39vb</locus>, 41rb, 45vb.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The name of the commissioner in the colophon
                     has been erased and replaced with that of Walda Māryām, written in a secondary
                     hand. The name of the original donors (among them probably Walda Māryām, cp.
                        23vb, 85va, 86rab) has been erased in the
                     supplication formulas and replaced with that of Walda ʾAbrǝham, in a secondary
                     hand, e.g., on 36ra, 41vb, 51ra, 81va.</provenance></history>
